A curated collection of boutique hotels in Mallorca, each built around a theme worth staying for. 🇪🇸

@castellsonclaret · Gastronomy. A Michelin-starred tasting menu inside a 19th-century castle, inspired by the nine winds of Mallorca.

@thelodgemallorca · Nature. 24 suites hidden across 157 hectares of lavender fields and ancient olive groves in a UNESCO private nature reserve.

@cancerahotel · City. A 17th-century palace in Palma’s old town. Just 14 rooms. Around the corner from the cathedral.

@sonbrull · Farm-to-table. An 18th-century monastery where the olive oil, wine and honey on your table were all grown on the estate.

@fincabanyols · Wellness. A 15th-century finca that opened in 2026. Spa treatments made with olive oil and honey from the land itself.

Send this to the person you’d explore Mallorca with.

Save it for your next trip to the island.

Drop a comment below where should I curate next?

